etymology.description: Originally 𫠤: 人(人) (rén, "person") with a headdress similar to 屮(屮) (chè, "sprout") -> stylized to resemble 夭(夭) (yāo, "young man") -> 攴(攴) (pū, "rap") added for authority -> stylized as 𢾍 -> 人(人) stylized as 方(方) (fāng, "square") -> final form 敖
etymology.interpretation: The character 敖 evolved from a pictogram to a phono-semantic compound by incorporating elements of authority and changing stylization over time, finally representing a man walking vigorously or travelling in an authoritative context.
